 compile\nnpm run lint    # No lint errors\n```\n\n---\n\n## Phase Requirements (All 12 Phases)\n\n### Phase 1: Basic FIFO Queue\n- Add tasks with payloads\n- Each task has: unique ID (UUID), status, creation timestamp\n- Tasks start in \"pending\" state\n- Retrieve next task → returns oldest pending task, transitions to \"processing\"\n- Return `null` if no tasks available\n- Check waiting task count\n\n### Phase 2: Named Queues\n- Tasks added to specific named queues\n- Default queue if no name provided\n- Each queue operates independently\n- Implicit queue creation on first task\n- List all queue names\n- Backward compatible with Phase 1\n\n### Phase 3: Priority\n- Priority levels 1-10 (1 = highest, 5 = default)\n- Higher priority (lower number) processed first\n- Same priority = FIFO order\n- Invalid priorities cause errors\n- Per-queue priority ordering\n- Task object exposes priority level\n\n### Phase 4: Delayed and Scheduled Tasks\n- Tasks with delay (milliseconds) or specific future time\n- Delayed tasks don't return until availability time passed\n- Non-delayed tasks preferred over delayed ones\n- Multiple delayed tasks ordered by: availability time → priority → FIFO\n- Task object shows availability time\n- Works with named queues\n\n### Phase 5: Retry with Backoff\n- Mark tasks as completed or failed\n- Failed tasks auto-retry with exponential backoff: `baseDelay * 2^(attempt - 1)`\n- Default: 3 retries, 1000ms base delay (both configurable per task)\n- Track attempt count\n- Retried tasks keep original queue and priority\n- Failed tasks after exhausting retries stay in failed state\n\n### Phase 6: Dead Letter Queue\n- Failed tasks (after retries exhausted) moved to DLQ\n- Per-queue DLQ\n- View dead-lettered tasks with error info and failure count\n- Move DLQ tasks back for fresh retries\n- Clear DLQ for a queue\n- Each queue has independent DLQ\n\n### Phase 7: Task Dependencies\n- Tasks can depend on other tasks\n- Task blocks until dependencies complete\n- Detect and reject circular dependencies at creation\n- Depending on non-existent task causes error\n- Failed dependency doesn't auto-fail dependents\n- Query dependency status\n\n### Phase 8: Concurrency Control\n- Per-queue concurrency limit\n- Limits tasks in \"processing\" state simultaneously\n- Retrieving task returns `null` if limit reached (even if pending tasks exist)\n- Unlimited by default\n- Set/query concurrency limit and active count\n- Works correctly with priority ordering\n\n### Phase 9: Progress Tracking and Cancellation\n- Processing tasks report progress (0-100%) with optional message\n- Query task's current progress\n- Subscribe to progress updates with notifications\n- Unsubscribe capability\n- Cancel pending or processing tasks\n- Cancelled pending tasks removed from queue\n- Cancelled processing tasks status updated\n- Cancelled tasks never retried\n\n### Phase 10: Recurring Tasks\n- Schedule tasks using simple cron expressions\n- Support: `*/N * * * *`, `0 * * * *`, `0 0 * * *`\n- Create, remove, list schedules\n- Manual \"tick\" mechanism for testing\n- Once enqueued, recurring tasks follow all queue rules\n- Removing schedule stops future occurrences\n\n### Phase 11: Middleware Pipeline\n- Register middleware per queue\n- Middleware receives task and \"next\" function\n- Can modify tasks or skip processing by not calling \"next\"\n- If middleware throws, task marked as failed\n- Per-queue processing handler registered\n- Independent middleware stack per queue\n\n### Phase 12: Graceful Shutdown\n- Signal system to stop accepting new tasks\n- Adding tasks after shutdown produces error\n- Wait for all processing tasks to finish (configurable timeout)\n- Force-cancel tasks exceeding timeout\n- Register shutdown callbacks\n- Produce shutdown summary: completed/force-cancelled counts and duration\n- Safe to call multiple times\n- Immediate completion if no tasks processing\n\n---\n\n## Source Code Status\n\n**Current State:** `/workspace/src/` is empty (only contains `.gitkeep`)\n\nNo existing implementation code to review. The project is ready for you to begin implementing from Phase 1.\n\n---\n\n## Key Design Considerations (from TASK.md)\n\n1. Later phases will force rethinks of early decisions → design with extensibility\n2. Tasks should have unique IDs and track lifecycle status\n3. Consider interactions between priorities, delays, and dependencies\n4. All implementation under `src/` directory\n5. Export main API from `src/index.ts`\n\nThis is a greenfield project requiring full implementation from scratch across 12 progressive phases."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad10dd6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 19200\ntool_uses: 22\nduration_ms: 26976</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"083d7f18-5302-4c12-9e84-dd21da35b9b0","uuid":"5c31160c-f21c-4620-bab0-32bdce906373","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the full project structure and context for this task queue system project. I need:\n1. All files in the project root and src/ directory\n2. Contents of package.json, tsconfig.json, and any config files\n3. All phase requirement files in phases/*.md - read ALL of them (phases 1-12)\n4. The TASK.md file\n5. Any existing source code in src/\n\nBe very thorough - read every phase file completely and every config file.","agentId":"ad10dd6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have completed a thorough exploration of the project. Here's the comprehensive project context:\n\n## Project Structure Overview\n\n**Root Directory:** `/workspace`\n\n**Key Files:**\n- `/workspace/package.json` - Project metadata and dependencies\n- `/workspace/tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration\n- `/workspace/vitest.config.ts` - Test configuration\n- `/workspace/.eslintrc.cjs` - Linting rules\n- `/workspace/TASK.md` - Main project overview\n- `/workspace/phases/` - Directory with 12 phase requirement files\n- `/workspace/src/` - Em