+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016jVhEEyBhrmQ8C8g8ZgDRr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Non-interactive mode: using Autopilot.\n\nThis is a substantial greenfield project with 12 phases of incremental complexity. Let me make the key design decisions and then write a comprehensive plan.\n\n**Key Design Decisions (Autopilot):**\n\n**Q: Overall architecture pattern?**\n→ Choosing: Single `TaskQueue` class with a `TaskQueueManager` for multi-queue support\nReasoning: A central manager handles named queues, each queue is an independent instance. This maps naturally to the phase progression - Phase 1 is a single queue, Phase 2 adds the manager.\n\n**Q: Task storage structure?**\n→ Choosing: Map<string, Task> for O(1) lookups by ID, with sorted retrieval logic for priority/delay\nReasoning: Tasks need frequent lookup by ID (dependencies, progress, cancellation) and ordered retrieval (priority, delay, FIFO).\n\n**Q: ID generation?**\n→ Choosing: `crypto.randomUUID()` - built-in Node.js, no dependencies\nReasoning: Requirement says UUID, Node.js has native support.\n\n**Q: Event/subscription system for progress?**\n→ Choosing: Simple EventEmitter pattern (custom implementation to avoid external deps)\nReasoning: Phase 9 needs subscriptions, Phase 12 needs shutdown callbacks. A lightweight event system serves both.\n\n**Q: Middleware pattern?**\n→ Choosing: Koa-style compose with next() function\nReasoning: Phase 11 explicitly describes middleware receiving task + next function.\n\n**Q: File organization?**\n→ Choosing: Modular files per concern, re-exported from index.ts\nReasoning: 12 phases of features will be too much for a single file. Separate files for Task, Queue, Manager, Scheduler, Middleware.\n\nLet me write the design document and then move to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1874,"cache_read_input_tokens":21