+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EvE3tqfbkMRzoU4DDbm63Y","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_015PKUQ2GtpqAFCodqTYaicX","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-07-task-queue-design.md","content":"# Task Queue System Design\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Core Types\n\n```typescript\ninterface Task {\n  id: string;              // crypto.randomUUID()\n  queue: string;           // queue name, default \"default\"\n  status: TaskStatus;      // pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled\n  payload: unknown;        // user-provided data\n  priority: number;        // 1-10, default 5 (lower = higher priority)\n  createdAt: Date;\n  updatedAt: Date;\n  availableAt?: Date;      // for delayed tasks\n  attempts: number;        // current attempt count\n  maxRetries: number;      // default 3\n  retryDelay: number;      // base delay in ms, default 1000\n  dependsOn: string[];     // task IDs this depends on\n  progress: number;        // 0-100\n  progressMessage?: string;\n  error?: string;          // last error message\n  failureCount: number;    // total failure count for DLQ\n}\n\ntype TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n```\n\n### File Structure\n\n- `src/index.ts` - Public API exports\n- `src/types.ts` - Type definitions\n- `src/task.ts` - Task creation and manipulation\n- `src/queue.ts` - Single queue implementation (FIFO, priority, delay, concurrency)\n- `src/manager.ts` - Multi-queue manager (named queues, DLQ access)\n- `src/scheduler.ts` - Recurring task scheduling (cron)\n- `src/middleware.ts` - Middleware pipeline\n- `src/cron-parser.ts` - Simple cron expression parser\n\n### Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **TaskQueue** class: Core queue with add/process/complete/fail methods\n2. **TaskQueueManager**: Factory/registry for named queues\n3. **Middleware compose**: Array of functions, composed into pipeline\n4. **EventEmitter-like**: For progress subscriptions and shutdown callbacks\n5. **Sorted retrieval**: Tasks retrieved by priority → availableAt → createdAt\n\n### Phase Integration Points\n\n- Phases 1-4: Core TaskQueue class grows incrementally\n- Phase 5-6: Add retry/DLQ logic to task completion flow\n- Phase 7: Dependency checking added to task retrieval\n- Phase 8: Concurrency guard on task retrieval\n- Phase 9: Progress tracking + cancellation on Task + Queue\n- Phase 10: Scheduler creates tasks on tick\n- Phase 11: Middleware wraps processing\n- Phase 12: Shutdown state flag + drain logic\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":535,"cache_read_input_tokens":23545,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":535},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"083d7f18-5302-4c12-9e84-dd21da35b9b0","uuid":"af37bc43-2b46-4e88-95c6-368da8cf907e"}
