+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012Mp4ia2bmow1kcwwKS2Uie","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Task Queue System Design\n     2→\n     3→## Architecture\n     4→\n     5→### Core Types\n     6→\n     7→```typescript\n     8→interface Task {\n     9→  id: string;              // crypto.randomUUID()\n    10→  queue: string;           // queue name, default \"default\"\n    11→  status: TaskStatus;      // pending | processing | completed | failed | cancelled\n    12→  payload: unknown;        // user-provided data\n    13→  priority: number;        // 1-10, default 5 (lower = higher priority)\n    14→  createdAt: Date;\n    15→  updatedAt: Date;\n    16→  availableAt?: Date;      // for delayed tasks\n    17→  attempts: number;        // current attempt count\n    18→  maxRetries: number;      // default 3\n    19→  retryDelay: number;      // base delay in ms, default 1000\n    20→  dependsOn: string[];     // task IDs this depends on\n    21→  progress: number;        // 0-100\n    22→  progressMessage?: string;\n    23→  error?: string;          // last error message\n    24→  failureCount: number;    // total failure count for DLQ\n    25→}\n    26→\n    27→type TaskStatus = 'pending' | 'processing' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled';\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→### File Structure\n    31→\n    32→- `src/index.ts` - Public API exports\n    33→- `src/types.ts` - Type definitions\n    34→- `src/task.ts` - Task creation and manipulation\n    35→- `src/queue.ts` - Single queue implementation (FIFO, priority, delay, concurrency)\n    36→- `src/manager.ts` - Multi-queue manager (named queues, DLQ access)\n    37→- `src/scheduler.ts` - Recurring task scheduling (cron)\n    38→- `src/middleware.ts` - Middleware pipeline\n    39→- `src/cron-parser.ts` - Simple cron expression parser\n    40→\n    41→### Key Design Patterns\n    42→\n    43→1. **TaskQueue** class: Core queue with add/process/complete/fail methods\n    44→2. **TaskQueueManager**: Factory/registry for named queues\n    45→3. **Middleware compose**: Array of functions, composed into pipeline\n    46→4. **EventEmitter-like**: For progress subscriptions and shutdown callbacks\n    47→5. **Sorted retrieval**: Tasks retrieved by priority → availableAt → createdAt\n    48→\n    49→### Phase Integration Points\n    50→\n    51→- Phases 1-4: Core TaskQueue class grows incrementally\n    52→- Phase 5-6: Add retry/DLQ logic to task completion flow\n    53→- Phase 7: Dependency checking added to task retrieval\n    54→- Phase 8: Concurrency guard on task retrieval\n    55→- Phase 9: Progress tracking + cancellation on Task + Queue\n    56→- Phase 10: Scheduler creates tasks on tick\n    57→- Phase 11: Middleware wraps processing\n    58→- Phase 12: Shutdown state flag + drain logic\n    59→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_018gV4vpnKRh9Xg9iuEFBrxw","session_id":"083d7f18-5302-4c12-9e84-dd21da35b9b0","uuid":"1a958a16-aef3-4634-b53d-e0a44f38b0b0"}
